definitions.definition: To collide or strike , the act of impinging .
examples: When the hammer impacts the nail, it bends.

definitions.definition: To compress ; to compact ; to press into something or pack together.
examples: The footprints of birds do not impact the soil in the way those of dinosaurs do.

definitions.definition: To significantly or strongly influence or affect ; to have an impact on.
examples: I can make the changes, but it will impact the schedule.

definitions.definition: To stamp or impress onto something.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To collide or strike , the act of impinging .
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To compress ; to compact ; to press into something or pack together.
( transitive , figurative , proscribed ) To significantly or strongly influence or affect ; to have an impact on.
( transitive , rare ) To stamp or impress onto something.
